[28.262964, "o", "ai_sast curated demo 0.2.0\r\r\ncases: 5\r\r\nphilosophy: candidate -> validate -> prove vulnerable or dismiss\r\r\nnote: This is a small curated demo scanned with the deterministic engine. When enabled, any LLM review is advisory only. It shows representative outcomes, not complete proof across arbitrary code bases.\r\r\n\r\r\n1. Confirmed issue\r\r\n   story: Direct user-controlled input reaches a command execution sink.\r\r\n   takeaway: The deterministic engine confirms the issue because no safety barrier is present.\r\r\n   deterministic:\r\r\n     file: /home/kingc/projects/demo/tests/demo/curated/confirmed_command.cpp:7\r\r\n     rule: command_injection.system\r\r\n     judgment: confirmed_issue confidence=0.94 deterministic=true\r\r\n     source: argv[1]\r\r\n     sink:   system(argv[1])\r\r\n     evidence: candidate only: configured sink system matched rule family command_injection; file path matches configured test marker; expression depends on parameter argv; expression references argv\r\r\n     explanation: positive vulnerability conditions were satisfied without a safety barrier\r\r\n   llm_review: not requested or not eligible\r\r\n\r\r\n2. Likely issue\r\r\n   story: User input reaches file-open code through a normalizer the engine does not yet trust as a fixed-root guard.\r\r\n   takeaway: Risk is real enough to escalate, but proof is still incomplete because the helper semantics are not modeled.\r\r\n   deterministic:\r\r\n     file: /home/kingc/projects/demo/tests/demo/curated/likely_issue_path.cpp:10\r\r\n     rule: path_traversal.file_open\r\r\n     judgment: likely_issue confidence=0.76 deterministic=false\r\r\n     source: normalize_path(argv[1])\r\r\n     sink:   fopen(normalize_path(argv[1]), \"r\")\r\r\n     evidence: candidate only: configured sink fopen matched rule family path_traversal; file path matches configured test marker; expression includes unmodeled helper call normalize_path; expression depends on parameter argv; expression references argv\r\r\n     explanation: path validation wrapper is not modeled\r\r\n     ambiguous_reasoning: path validation wrapper is not modeled\r\r\n   llm_review:\r\r\n     provider_status: ok\r\r\n     judgment: likely_issue confidence=0.76\r\r\n     reasoning: Deterministic judgment remains likely_issue because the compact context shows elevated risk at the sink, but the proof is still incomplete. Risk signal: user-controlled path reaches file sink. Unresolved point: path validation wrapper is not modeled.\r\r\n     remediation: Constrain the path under a fixed trusted root immediately before the file-open sink and reject escapes from that root.\r\r\n\r\r\n3. Needs review\r\r\n   story: A bounded copy uses a runtime length the engine cannot prove against the destination extent.\r\r\n   takeaway: This stays uncertain until a human reviewer or stronger range analysis can prove the bound.\r\r\n   deterministic:\r\r\n     file: /home/kingc/projects/demo/tests/demo/curated/needs_review_string.cpp:15\r\r\n     rule: dangerous_string.unbounded_copy\r\r\n     judgment: needs_review confidence=0.58 deterministic=false\r\r\n     source: argv[1]\r\r\n     sink:   memcpy(destination, argv[1], length)\r\r\n     evidence: candidate only: configured sink memcpy matched rule family dangerous_string; file path matches configured test marker; expression depends on parameter argv; expression references argv; copy length expression length\r\r\n     explanation: copy bound expression could not be proven against the destination extent\r\r\n     ambiguous_reasoning: copy bound expression could not be proven against the destination extent\r\r\n   llm_review:\r\r\n     provider_status: ok\r\r\n     judgment: needs_review confidence=0.58\r\r\n     reasoning: Deterministic judgment remains needs_review because the compact context could not be proven safe and requires review. Safety of the bound is not established.\r\r\n     remediation: Check the runtime length against the destination extent before the memcpy-style sink, or tie the bound directly to sizeof(destination).\r\r\n\r\r\n4. Likely safe\r\r\n   story: A path guard removes simple traversal patterns before file access, but the engine does not treat it as a full fixed-root proof.\r\r\n   takea"]
[28.263132, "o", "way: Safety evidence exists, so the result leans safe without claiming complete proof.\r\r\n   deterministic:\r\r\n     file: /home/kingc/projects/demo/tests/demo/curated/likely_safe_path.cpp:15\r\r\n     rule: path_traversal.file_open\r\r\n     judgment: likely_safe confidence=0.78 deterministic=false\r\r\n     source: argv[1]\r\r\n     sink:   fopen(path.c_str(), \"r\")\r\r\n     evidence: candidate only: configured sink fopen matched rule family path_traversal; file path matches configured test marker; value resolves through local path = argv[1]; expression depends on parameter argv; expression references argv; allowlist predicate is_safe_path observed for path\r\r\n     explanation: path allowlist predicate constrains user input\r\r\n     safe_reasoning: path allowlist predicate constrains user input\r\r\n     ambiguous_reasoning: path allowlist exists but root confinement proof is incomplete\r\r\n   llm_review:\r\r\n     provider_status: ok\r\r\n     judgment: likely_safe confidence=0.78\r\r\n     reasoning: Deterministic judgment remains likely_safe because the compact context shows a safety signal near the sink, but the proof is still incomplete. Current safety signal: path allowlist predicate constrains user input. Remaining gap: path allowlist exists but root confinement proof is incomplete.\r\r\n     safe_reasoning: path allowlist predicate constrains user input\r\r\n     remediation: For a stronger safety proof, canonicalize the path under a fixed trusted root immediately before the file-open sink.\r\r\n\r\r\n5. Safe / suppressed\r\r\n   story: User input reaches file-open code, but the validator proves the path is constrained under a fixed root.\r\r\n   takeaway: A lookalike path traversal pattern is dismissed because the safety barrier is explicit and provable.\r\r\n   deterministic:\r\r\n     file: /home/kingc/projects/demo/tests/demo/curated/safe_dismissed.cpp:14\r\r\n     rule: path_traversal.file_open\r\r\n     judgment: safe_suppressed confidence=0.98 deterministic=true\r\r\n     source: canonicalize_under_root(argv[1], \"/srv/demo-root\")\r\r\n     sink:   fopen(path.c_str(), \"r\")\r\r\n     evidence: candidate only: configured sink fopen matched rule family path_traversal; file path matches configured test marker; value resolves through local path = canonicalize_under_root(argv[1], \"/srv/demo-root\"); expression flows through configured sanitizer canonicalize_under_root; expression depends on parameter argv; expression references argv\r\r\n     explanation: canonicalized path is confined under a fixed root\r\r\n     safe_reasoning: canonicalized path is confined under a fixed root\r\r\n   llm_review: not requested or not eligible\r\r\n\r\r\ntakeaway:\r\r\n- confirmed_issue: direct untrusted input reaches a dangerous sink without a safety barrier.\r\r\n- likely_issue: risk evidence is strong, but proof is still incomplete.\r\r\n- needs_review: the engine cannot yet prove the code safe or unsafe.\r\r\n- likely_safe: safety evidence exists, but it is not yet a full proof.\r\r\n- safe_suppressed: the validator proved a concrete safety barrier and dismissed the candidate.\r\r\n\r\r\n\r\r\n\r\r\n1. Scan repository\r\r\n2. Scan single C++ file\r\r\n3. Scan with engine only (choose target)\r\r\n4. Scan with engine + LLM review (choose target)\r\r\n5. Run demo case\r\r\n6. Setup & tutorials\r\r\n7. Exit\r\r\nSelect an option [1-7]: "]
